[SN]TITLE[SN]
FTSE 100 opens flat as China's currency strengthens

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
(Open): Shares on London's main index were flat in early trading.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The FTSE 100 index was down by just one point at 6,567.35.
Mining firm Glencore was the biggest faller, down 1.9% while chip maker Arm Holdings was the best performer, up 2.8%.
Overnight, China's central bank increased the range in which its currency, the yuan, could trade, allowing it to strengthen, after three days of falls.
Earlier this week China devalued the currency sparking falls on stock markets.
